;P&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D=\r\n2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Namaste friends,&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT colo=\r\nr=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;=\r\nFONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;This is a small writeup on &quot;si=\r\nddhis&quot; vis-a-vis spiritual progress, in reaction to further exchanges on Tw=\r\nitter. This is a delicate area where many have misconceptions and I will tr=\r\ny to address them.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 siz=\r\ne=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#0=\r\n00000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *=\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft=\r\n&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV ali=\r\ngn=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Maharshi Vasishtha&#39;=\r\ns teaching to Lord Rama is clear in Yoga Vaasishtham. The goal of existence=\r\n and sadhana is self-realization. Siddhis are to be neither specifically so=\r\nught nor specifically avoided, by a seeker of Self. If Nature gives one som=\r\ne siddhi(s), one should accept them with neither excitement nor disappointm=\r\nent. But one should NOT run after them, for they are neither necessary nor =\r\nsufficient for self-realization and liberation.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dl=\r\neft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV =\r\nalign=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Vivekananda used=\r\n the same principle when Ramakirishna proposed to give his siddhis to Vivek=\r\nananda. He asked whether the siddhis will enable him to realize god. Ramakr=\r\nishna said no. Vivekananda firmly declined the offer then! Of course, when =\r\nRamakrishna gave them anyway later, he accepted them. Vivekananda&#39;s two act=\r\nions demonstrate Vasishtha&#39;s instructions well.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dl=\r\neft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV =\r\nalign=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/=\r\nFONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana=\r\n&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=\r\n=3DVerdana&gt;Let us use the analogy of climbing a hill. Climbing hill is one&#39;=\r\ns spiritual sadhana. Reaching the top is liberation. Different people climb=\r\n the hill from different sides and using different paths. There may be tree=\r\ns with nice fruits on the sides of the road. They are siddhis or special ab=\r\nilities.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=\r\n=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=\r\n=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;If one gets distracted, starts climbing the trees and c=\r\nollecting fruits, one&#39;s journey gets delayed and one may not reach the top.=\r\n That is why Vasishtha says a seeker of Self does not pursue any siddhis.&lt;/=\r\nFONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana=\r\n&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=\r\n=3DVerdana&gt;But if some fruits fall in one&#39;s lap by themselves, one can keep=\r\n them. Similarly, siddhis that come to one by themselves can be accepted by=\r\n a seeker of Self.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 siz=\r\ne=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#0=\r\n00000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Now an important distinction:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;D=\r\nIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;=\r\n&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Ther=\r\ne are some trees that are found at lower altitudes also, but some really sp=\r\necial trees are found at very high altitudes only. If one has such a fruit,=\r\n it shows that one has climbed great heights. Similarly, some siddhis do no=\r\nt mean much, but some siddhis are very special and only really elevated sad=\r\nhakas can obtain them (whether by trying or without trying). If a sadhakas =\r\ndemonstrates such a siddhi, you can see that one progressed a lot. However,=\r\n the key is that one who climbed the same or more distance may not have tha=\r\nt or any other fruit. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000=\r\n size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=\r\n=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=\r\n=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;=\r\nDIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Unlike in th=\r\ne example of climbing hill, which is an external activity, spiritual progre=\r\nss in real life is *internal*. There is NO way for anyone to know for sure =\r\nhow much progress one has made, how much self-control one has internally an=\r\nd what exactly goes on in one&#39;s mind. We may try to judge it from external =\r\nfactors such as actions, words etc, but it is not necessarily accurate.&lt;/FO=\r\nNT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&=\r\nnbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3D=\r\nVerdana&gt;Here, some people swayed by siddhis may be tempted to use one&#39;s sid=\r\ndhis to judge how high one climbed. But that is faulty. One person who reac=\r\nhed the absolute top may not have any fruits, while one person who still ha=\r\ns ways to climb may have gotten some really nice fruit. Using externaslly d=\r\nemonstrable siddhis that are neither necessary nor sufficient for Self-real=\r\nization as a measure of one&#39;s progress is unsound.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=\r\n=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;=\r\nDIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Given that s=\r\npiritual progress is internal, how can we judge it and compare people then?=\r\n Well, we need not and should not. Only a sarvaantaryaami - a perfected bei=\r\nng who has access to each being&#39;s internal state - can do that.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV=\r\n&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/F=\r\nONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;=\r\n*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D=\r\n2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#00000=\r\n0 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Rajarshi, you are assuming that Ramakrishna Param=\r\nahamsa is a Paramahamsa on Vimalananda&#39;s scale. You are concluding that Ram=\r\nakrishna is a Paramahamsa; Abhedananda, Vivekananda etc are lower than that=\r\n; Vimalananda is a rishi; and hence Vimalananda is superior to Abhedananda =\r\nand Vivekananda by 2pwr16 to 2.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=\r\n=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;F=\r\nONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Is Paramahamsa Nithyananda, who=\r\n was caught in a sex scandal, also a Paramahamsa because he is known so? Se=\r\ne, how people are famously known may or may not reflect their spiritual sta=\r\nture. Real spiritual stature is internal and you cannot see it.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV=\r\n&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/F=\r\nONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;=\r\nWe do not know who Ramakrishna Paramahamsa really is. He may not be just a =\r\nparamahamsa on Vimalananda&#39;s scale, but be a siddha or a natha or even a ri=\r\nshi. He may even be Vishnu himself, as he himself said and some religious e=\r\nxperts of that time declared based on various signs. If Ramakrishna Paramah=\r\namsa is Vishnu himself, Vivekananda, Abhedananda etc can definitely be rish=\r\nis or naths in Vimalananda&#39;s scale. If your argument is that they cannot be=\r\n because they did not demonstrate siddhis compatible with that status, that=\r\n is a non-point as I explained above. The disagreement between then boils d=\r\nown a difference in the relevance and importance of externally demonstrated=\r\n siddhis.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 fac=\r\ne=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 siz=\r\ne=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT co=\r\nlor=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft=\r\n&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Why this is relevant and I s=\r\npent some time on this is that some people seem to have misconceptions. The=\r\n take home for some people from some books describing miracles and siddhis =\r\nmay be that siddhis are important.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT col=\r\nor=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;=\r\n&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Vasishtha is not only a rishi=\r\n, but one of saptarshis. Please read what he taught Lord Rama in Yoga Vaasi=\r\nshtham. It is the essence of Veda and Upanishad. It will balance your views=\r\n and mould your attitude. Read Yoga Vaasishtham. Siddhis are neither necess=\r\nary nor sufficient for self-realization. Don&#39;t be distracted by them or be =\r\ninfatuated with them.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 =\r\nsize=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=\r\n=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;The goal of sadhana is that your notions=\r\n of &quot;this is I and these are mine&quot; get subtler and subtler and hold of six =\r\ninternal enemies on you becomes weaker and weaker. Others may or may not be=\r\n able to see and judge your progress, but you know your progress and weakne=\r\nsses the best. THAT is the crux and siddhis have no relevance or meaning. A=\r\nny fascination for them will set you back in your sadhana.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DI=\r\nV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;=\r\n/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;Best =\r\nregards,&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=\r\n=3DVerdana&gt;Narasimha&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 s=\r\nize=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;----------------------------------------------------=\r\n---------------&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=\r\n=