uperior to so and so thing taught by Shiva, etc. B=\r\nut we &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=\r\n=3DVerdana&gt;&gt; know that none of the hierarchies is absolute.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;=\r\n\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&gt; &lt;/FON=\r\nT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&g=\r\nt; One who has the nerve to think that one can compare the wisdom of &lt;/FONT=\r\n&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&gt=\r\n; Jnaneshwar, dispassion of Ramana Maharshi, mad devotion of Ramakrishna &lt;/=\r\nFONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana=\r\n&gt;&gt; Paramahamsa, detached activism of Vivekananda, compassion of Shirdi S=\r\nai, &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DV=\r\nerdana&gt;&gt; spiritual ecstasy of Vama Khepa, inner clarity of Lahiri Mahash=\r\naya, &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3D=\r\nVerdana&gt;&gt; detachment of Trilinga Swami, purity of Tukaram, humility of E=\r\nknath &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=\r\n=3DVerdana&gt;&gt; Maharaj, ecstatic love of Meera Bai, motherly love of Gopal=\r\ner Ma, etc, &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 =\r\nface=3DVerdana&gt;&gt; is a fool of the highest order. They can be compared fr=\r\nom specific &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 =\r\nface=3DVerdana&gt;&gt; limited perspectives. In one thing, Tukaram may be supe=\r\nrior to all, in &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=\r\n=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&gt; another Jnaneshwar, in another Trilinga, in anothe